<subSubSection id="C322B8883A05FF9CFF0AEE01FD72FE3F" pageId="5" pageNumber="1138" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B87EB033A05FF9CFF0AEE01FD72FE3F" blockId="5.[178,1085,319,488]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1138">
Comment: According to 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA996F23A05FF9CFE52EE01FD20FE8D" author="COIFFAIT H" box="[490,662,319,341]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1138" pagination="135 - 150" refId="ref27945" refString="COIFFAIT H. (1968): Coleopteres Staphylinides recoltes par J. Mateu dans l'Ennedi. - Bulletin de l'I. F. A. N., ser. A 30 (1): 135 - 150." type="journal article" year="1968">COIFFAIT (1968)</bibRefCitation>
, the type material is composed of a male 
<typeStatus id="548355A13A05FF9CFF0AEE1CFEBDFEAB" box="[178,267,349,371]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1138">holotype</typeStatus>
and 
<specimenCount id="9D3E208A3A05FF9CFEFAEE1CFE00FEAB" box="[322,438,349,371]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1138" type="female">two female</specimenCount>
<typeStatus id="548355A13A05FF9CFE78EE1CFD97FEAA" box="[448,545,349,370]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1138">paratypes</typeStatus>
from &quot;Borkou, Bir Nazara&quot; and 
<specimenCount id="9D3E208A3A05FF9CFCC6EE1CFC6AFEAB" box="[894,988,349,371]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1138" type="male">one male</specimenCount>
<typeStatus id="548355A13A05FF9CFC5EEE1CFB8BFEAA" box="[998,1085,349,370]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1138">paratype</typeStatus>
from &quot;Ennedi, guelta de Guir Kaqué&quot;. The above material from Tibesti and 
<collectingCountry id="F32FAB933A05FF9CFC5AEE3AFBBDFE48" box="[994,1035,379,400]" name="Iran" pageId="5" pageNumber="1138">Iran</collectingCountry>
was standing as 
<taxonomicName id="4C3890803A05FF9CFE92EED9FE13FE74" authorityName="PEYERIMHOFF" authorityYear="1929" box="[298,421,407,429]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lithocharis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="1138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fontinalis">
<emphasis id="B94C37113A05FF9CFE92EED9FE13FE74" box="[298,421,407,429]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1138">L. fontinalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the Jarrige collection at the MNHNP. For an additional record from 
<collectingCountry id="F32FAB933A05FF9CFF56EEF4FE81FE12" box="[238,311,437,458]" name="Yemen" pageId="5" pageNumber="1138">Yemen</collectingCountry>
see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA996F23A05FF9CFED4EEF4FDA0FE13" author="ASSING V" box="[364,534,437,459]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1138" pagination="973 - 986" refId="ref27503" refString="ASSING V. (2012 b): On the Staphylinidae of Socotra Island, Yemen (Insecta: Coleoptera). - Linzer Biologische Beitrage 44 (2): 973 - 986." type="journal article" year="2012">ASSING (2012b)</bibRefCitation>
. The habitus and the primary and secondary sexual characters of the 
<typeStatus id="548355A13A05FF9CFED8EE93FE0FFE30" box="[352,441,466,488]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1138">holotype</typeStatus>
are illustrated in 
<figureCitation id="1303F7863A05FF9CFDD2EE93FD76FE3F" box="[618,704,466,488]" captionStart="Figs 1-7" captionStartId="5.[178,218,1537,1559]" captionTargetBox="[213,1050,753,1514]" captionTargetId="figure-266@5.[208,1056,753,1524]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 1-7: Lithocharis mateui COIFFAIT, holotype: (1) habitus; (2) male sternite VII; (3) male sternite VIII; (4) posterior portion of male sternite VIII; (5-6) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (7) basal portion of ventral process in ventral view. Scale bars: 1: 1.0 mm; 2-6: 0.2 mm; 7: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5184184" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5184184/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="1138">Figs 1-7</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
